line_1: Will MANSFIELD take this Virtue for thy bail?
line_2: Or by base blund'ring Statesmen sent to jail,

line_1: Run out as fast, as one that pays his Bail
line_2: And dreads more Actions, hurries from a Jail.

line_1: For want of good sufficient bail;
line_2: Hath let my debtor rot in jail,

line_1: Who rashly stood his smooth-tongu'd brother's bail:
line_2: Turn to yon prison! list yon captive's tale,
